WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.520
è fondata. E quindi, per essere in grado di svegliare e mobilizzare di nuovo le risorse simboliche

00:06.520 --> 00:15.640
di significazione, è venuta per noi, più e più, uno dei modi per raggiungere gli obiettivi

00:15.640 --> 00:22.660
e le idee dei fondatori. Grazie molto, e grazie a Presidente Prodi, di nuovo, per essere qui.

00:30.780 --> 00:40.660
Ok, buongiorno a tutti. È davvero un onore per me essere qui, in questo templo di scienze,

00:40.660 --> 00:50.040
e per inaugurare questo maestro di degree in internazionale di sicurezza, che è una cosa

00:50.040 --> 01:10.640
nuova in Italia, molto selezionale, e penso che sarà molto utile creare l'elite necessaria

01:11.200 --> 01:19.140
Non è la prima volta che parlo in fronte di un pubblico che sa molto di più di ciò che faccio,

01:19.440 --> 01:29.340
perché ogni politico fa ciò. Ma comunque, in questo caso è particolarmente, diciamo,

01:29.340 --> 01:46.420
molto imbarazzante, ma io solo giustifico me, dicendo che la mia ignoranza è enciclopedica,

01:46.420 --> 02:00.220
quindi posso bilanciarmi. Guardate, abbiamo 40 minuti per parlare di l'evoluzione della politica mondiale

02:00.220 --> 02:10.680
e del ruolo d'Europa. Prima di tutto, sono così, diciamo, sorpreso, ma anche,

02:10.680 --> 02:23.540
you know, find it normal that almost everybody in the political science elite has some nostalgia

02:24.580 --> 02:32.980
about the Cold War. The nostalgia for the Cold War is coming back as a mantra, you know,

02:34.540 --> 02:40.520
and if you think that during the Cold War, of course the young student, they don't remember it,

02:40.520 --> 02:54.640
but we were living frightened by the idea of a nuclear explosion, a big clash, a nuclear war and so on and so on and so on.

02:55.000 --> 03:05.180
And so this nostalgia means that something wrong went in history after the end of the Cold War.

03:06.050 --> 03:19.480
And the reasons of nostalgia is that after that we passed from the Cold War to the Monopolar War,

03:19.700 --> 03:32.160
you know, Monopolar War that, say, United States were the only power able to run the war and could alone do it.

03:32.160 --> 03:42.860
This was the common opinion. And to the, you know, to the scholars, they can remind two publications,

03:43.260 --> 03:51.580
one the end of history and the other one the American Century. The meaning was the same.

03:51.580 --> 04:02.740
We entering in a period of end of history because there will be at least an American Century.

04:03.520 --> 04:11.580
American Century meaning that one country could have dominated the world alone.

04:12.780 --> 04:16.840
And history went in a different way, you know.

04:18.500 --> 04:28.420
Well, let's just go back a bit. And this opinion was shared not only by some intellectual,

04:28.600 --> 04:37.880
but was shared by political leadership, you know, and I do think I am convinced that the Iraqi War,

04:37.880 --> 04:46.280
it was simply the concrete manifestation of monopolarity.

04:47.300 --> 04:57.920
The idea that you could put the seal of the American domination in a war easy to win,

04:58.900 --> 05:06.520
that was supposed to endure a few weeks, and that was the seal of the American power.

05:06.520 --> 05:12.840
And things went different since that moment. Then we can quote the Afghanistan War,

05:13.140 --> 05:22.400
but any case of bringing a war outside the country, you know, in a foreign place,

05:23.320 --> 05:32.040
it demonstrated that the challenge of a country to dominate the world

05:32.040 --> 05:40.340
was much more difficult than any political scientist could imagine, you know.

05:41.980 --> 05:49.560
And since the moment there was the starting of dangerous local, non-local conflicts,

05:49.840 --> 05:54.820
local in the sense that they were not world war, but non-local,

05:54.820 --> 06:03.940
because all these conflicts from Iraq to Afghanistan, they completely moved the structure

06:03.940 --> 06:15.480
of the political structure of the states that were around the place in which the war started.

06:15.480 --> 06:25.580
And this conflict, they eroded a lot of the American strength.

06:26.540 --> 06:38.540
Look, I have to be clear, U.S. Army and U.S. strength, U.S. leadership is strong even now.

06:38.540 --> 06:46.360
The United States is the strongest country in the world, by far.

06:47.700 --> 06:51.560
The military expenditure of the United States, depending upon strategy,

06:52.120 --> 06:59.640
is from 43 to 50 percent of all the world military budget.

07:00.700 --> 07:03.180
The technology is by far the more advanced.

07:03.180 --> 07:07.360
But the society changed.

07:09.180 --> 07:15.580
Well, second, United States is the only country that has, let's say,

07:17.020 --> 07:20.120
avant-posts and troops everywhere in the world.

07:21.340 --> 07:30.580
I don't know whether there are 600 or 800 American, let's say, barracks

07:30.580 --> 07:35.300
expanded in the world, but there is no other case.

07:36.220 --> 07:46.700
But in spite of that, U.S. is unable to exercise, in practical terms,

07:46.700 --> 07:53.880
this power for a simple reason.

07:54.300 --> 08:02.080
Because of this negative event of the Bush and post-Bush wars,

08:03.240 --> 08:14.540
the American society is absolutely against any idea of having back dead bodies

08:14.540 --> 08:17.920
from abroad, Republican, Democratic.

08:18.260 --> 08:22.580
I think even Trump cannot tell to the electorate,

08:23.560 --> 08:32.200
we shall have again young Americans died coming back from the various world countries.

08:33.240 --> 08:38.940
And this is a change, a total change in the world strategy.

08:38.940 --> 08:45.440
Now you have United States that are very active with the drones,

08:45.760 --> 08:50.240
with the planes, with bombing, but not with the boots.

08:51.920 --> 08:58.240
And you cannot take the power of the world without boots,

08:58.860 --> 09:01.860
without direct influence.

09:01.860 --> 09:10.860
And this is the major change,

09:13.880 --> 09:20.060
but clearly does not mean that the American is becoming isolationist.

09:20.240 --> 09:25.240
Maybe with Trump could be more isolationist,

09:25.240 --> 09:33.180
but I think that even Trump cannot go too far in this direction

09:33.180 --> 09:40.680
because the military and even more economic links

09:40.680 --> 09:43.640
with the United States, with the rest of the world,

09:45.300 --> 09:49.580
Europe, China and everywhere is too deep now

09:49.580 --> 09:54.420
and any really isolationist policy

09:54.980 --> 09:59.980
could devastate really the American economy.

10:00.540 --> 10:09.380
So don't trust literally what Trump is expressing in the campaign

10:09.380 --> 10:19.500
because he cannot put to the end of the meaning.

10:22.100 --> 10:29.920
And certainly the foreign American policy

10:29.920 --> 10:34.700
has been from some, even under Obama

10:34.700 --> 10:37.960
has been from many point of view disappointing.

10:39.440 --> 10:44.220
He started with a great scenario, great engagement

10:44.220 --> 10:48.320
if you think only to the Cairo speech about Africa.

10:48.600 --> 10:53.720
He has given really hope, a great hope to all the African countries

10:53.720 --> 10:57.620
and nothing happened, almost nothing happened.

10:58.880 --> 11:05.020
Clearly Obama has been engaged more to try to

11:06.100 --> 11:10.180
let's say slim down the Bush heritage

11:10.560 --> 11:12.640
than to do something new.

11:13.700 --> 11:16.500
And this work was going too long.

11:17.320 --> 11:20.100
Probably it was too slow only in the last year.

11:20.500 --> 11:24.300
He's taken some initiative with Iran, nuclear base,

11:24.300 --> 11:27.940
but look in the end of the mandate

11:27.940 --> 11:34.700
in which the power of the president is not so important.

11:40.060 --> 11:48.500
But in spite of the internal fairly successful policy

11:48.500 --> 11:54.760
not only even if with big dangers for the budget for the future

11:54.760 --> 11:58.060
he has given new health system to

11:59.380 --> 12:01.840
dozens of millions of people

12:01.840 --> 12:06.720
and lucky for him

12:06.720 --> 12:12.380
but a new energy policy made United States stronger than before

12:12.380 --> 12:16.600
and in the end United States

12:17.980 --> 12:23.220
overcame the crisis much better than any other big power in the world.

12:24.680 --> 12:27.080
Don't forget that the crisis started

12:27.620 --> 12:32.520
and was originated by United States

12:32.520 --> 12:37.420
but United States went out quickly, very quickly

12:37.420 --> 12:46.880
because let's say different from the American tradition of Reagan

12:46.880 --> 12:51.580
they put $800 billion on the table immediately

12:51.580 --> 12:53.500
to react to the crisis.

12:56.040 --> 12:58.540
Obama overcame the crisis

12:58.540 --> 13:03.320
with some sort that we could call Keynesian policy

13:03.320 --> 13:10.160
not policy like the predecessor and the new energy policy.

13:10.940 --> 13:12.980
Of course the shale gas and shale oil

13:12.980 --> 13:16.100
have been a blessing for the American economy

13:16.320 --> 13:19.620
but in spite of that

13:19.620 --> 13:29.480
I repeat, no possibility of being dominating on the policy

13:29.480 --> 13:32.660
and last observation

13:32.660 --> 13:37.980
the moving of the core attention

13:38.400 --> 13:42.940
in theory from the Atlantic to the Pacific

13:42.940 --> 13:45.560
the obsession with China

13:45.560 --> 13:48.760
they moved and all the problems came from here

13:48.760 --> 13:50.060
and not from there

13:50.060 --> 13:52.740
it was a strange situation

13:53.760 --> 13:55.940
China is an obsession

13:55.940 --> 13:59.760
but the problem they come from Middle East and Europe

13:59.760 --> 14:03.470
from the Mediterranean and from the Middle East

14:08.940 --> 14:14.060
so with this lot of proxy wars

14:14.060 --> 14:18.900
in which Americans are not engaged mainly

14:18.900 --> 14:24.280
and they try to engage less and less

14:24.280 --> 14:25.780
but they are still engaged

14:26.640 --> 14:28.540
the last example of that

14:29.440 --> 14:33.880
I insist on that because it is a great change of the world

14:33.880 --> 14:37.500
if you take the Iraqi war

14:37.500 --> 14:44.660
the United States spent 90% of the cost of the world

14:44.660 --> 14:46.760
could be 85, could be 95

14:47.280 --> 14:50.040
if you take the Libya one

14:50.040 --> 14:57.020
the cost was 15% France, 15% UK

14:57.020 --> 15:01.400
15% United States, 10% Italy

15:01.400 --> 15:04.420
and then Gulf and so on

15:04.420 --> 15:08.080
so you have this engagement

15:08.980 --> 15:14.240
and Obama also repented

15:14.240 --> 15:19.200
he blamed himself for having accepted

15:19.200 --> 15:21.180
to enter into this war

15:21.180 --> 15:25.020
he tried to disengage from this foreign policy

15:25.020 --> 15:28.920
but it is some sort of heritage of the past

15:28.920 --> 15:32.640
from which they could disengage

15:32.640 --> 15:34.520
but in the meanwhile

15:34.950 --> 15:37.140
when these things went on

15:37.140 --> 15:39.280
the world has changed

15:39.280 --> 15:40.760
the world has changed

15:40.760 --> 15:43.220
first of all China

15:44.560 --> 15:48.060
China is really the new fact

15:48.760 --> 15:50.600
the new event of the world

15:53.140 --> 15:55.500
growth, not only growth

15:55.500 --> 15:58.080
but also technological change

15:58.620 --> 16:02.080
the scientific role of China will become dominant

16:02.760 --> 16:04.100
even that in the future

16:04.760 --> 16:08.800
but a country who arrived to the world

16:08.800 --> 16:12.180
with a completely different strategy

16:12.800 --> 16:16.140
arrived, I am inexact

16:16.140 --> 16:17.660
came back again

16:17.660 --> 16:22.640
